MOSCOW, Feb. 7 (Xinhua) -- A gas leak caused a blast in a residential building in western Russia's Tula region on Tuesday, killing at least five people and injuring three others, the Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations said. The five-storey building in the city of Efremov partially collapsed in the explosion and seven people have been rescued so far, the ministry said in a statement. Two points of temporary accommodation have been set up, and psychologists and rescuers are still working at the scene.  â– 